  "prompt": "What is a suitable inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center in Cherokee County AL?",
  "response": "As of my last update, I don't have real-time access to specific directories or databases. However, I can offer some general advice on finding a suitable inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center in Cherokee County, AL:\n\n1. **Check with Local Resources**: Contact local health departments or community health centers in Cherokee County for recommendations. They often have listings of nearby rehab facilities.\n\n2. **Consult Your Physician**: A healthcare provider can often recommend reputable treatment centers based on your specific needs.\n\n3. **Search Online Databases**: Websites like the Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration (SAMHSA) provide online tools to locate treatment facilities by area.\n\n4. **Insurance Provider**: Contact your health insurance provider to find in-network facilities, which could help manage costs.\n\n5. **Phone Helplines**: National helplines, such as the SAMHSA helpline (1-800-662-HELP), can provide guidance and referrals.\n\n6. **Community Support Groups**: Organizations such as Alcoholics Anonymous (AA) or Narcotics Anonymous (NA) may have local chapters that can suggest local treatment options.\n\nPlease verify any information through direct communication with facilities to ensure they meet your specific treatment needs and criteria.",
